\citation{demsar2006}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Mean \textbf  {(a)} training and \textbf  {(b)} inference time (seconds, log scale) over the twenty datasets on a single GPU. SCMK$_{K=1}$ is the single-kernel variant; KFGOD and DFNO are transductive and appear only under inference. SCMK's multiple-kernel training cost ($3.07$\,s) stays below NeuTraLAD and ICL, and its inference ($11$\,ms) is among the fastest---far below the transductive KFGOD ($1.96$\,s) and DFNO ($0.28$\,s).}}{21}{}\protected@file@percent }
